m_q.target_metric: Maximum aluminum value (Al column) from climate dataset, rounded to 4 decimal places
sub_questions: Find most northern Neolithic sample in Maltese dataset
Find closest year(s) in climate dataset Age_ky column
Calculate max Al value across those years

schema_conflicts: Different time units: radiocarbon uses years BP (date), climate uses kiloyears (Age_ky)
No direct join columns between datasets

scale_issues: Age_ky in climate data needs conversion to years for comparison with radiocarbon dates
Multiple Age_ky columns (Age_ky, Age_ky.1, Age_ky.2, Age_ky.3) with potentially different values
cross_source_conflicts: Time scale mismatch: radiocarbon dates vs geological ages
Which Age_ky column to use for year matching?

format_notes: radiocarbon_database_regional.xlsx has Greek character ΔR in column names
Longitude column is object type (may contain non-numeric values)

constraints: Must handle multiple closest years in climate data
Must convert Age_ky to years for comparison
Must handle ties in northernmost samples by taking later date
derived_filters: Filter radiocarbon data: Culture == 'Neolithic' AND (Region contains 'Malta' OR Site contains 'Malta')
Filter climate data: Use Age_ky column (not Age_ky.1, Age_ky.2, Age_ky.3) for year matching
statistical_tests: Check for duplicate Age_ky values in climate data
Verify Al values are numeric and not missing
output_format_requirements: Final answer must be rounded to 4 decimal places
Must handle case where multiple climate years are equally close to target year
